    "details": {
      "en": {
        "id": "en",
        "purpose": "To calculate the total sum for the Modified Minnesota Detoxification Scale (mMINDS).",
        "keywords": [
          "modified",
          "Minnesota",
          "detoxification",
          "scale",
          "mMINDS",
          "ICU",
          "intensive",
          "care",
          "critical",
          "alcohol",
          "withdrawal",
          "symptom"
        ],
        "use": "The mMINDS assesses 9 parameteres  to determine the severity of alcohol withdrawal symptoms:\n- pulse\n- diastolic blood pressure\n- the presence of tremor\n- sweating\n- hallucinations\n- agitation : measured using the Richmond Agitation-Sedation Scale (RASS)\n- disorientation \n- delusions\n- seizures \n\nThe maximum score is 46.\n\nThe mMINDS does not require the patient to answer questions or follow commands, making it well-suited for patients with alcohol withdrawal severe enough to require ICU-level care.",
        "misuse": "Not to be used for calculation of the original Minnesota Detoxification Scale (MINDS).",
        "copyright": "© Cambio CDS"
      }
    },
    "other_details": {
      "references": "Littlefield AJ, Heavner MS, Eng CC, Cooper DA, Heavner JJ, Kurtz JM, Pisani MA. Correlation Between mMINDS and CIWA-Ar Scoring Tools in Patients With Alcohol Withdrawal Syndrome. Am J Crit Care. 2018 Jul;27(4):280-286. doi: 10.4037/ajcc2018547. PMID: 29961663.\n\nDeCarolis DD, Rice KL, Ho L, Willenbring ML, Cassaro S. Symptom-driven lorazepam protocol for treatment of severe alcohol withdrawal delirium in the intensive care unit. Pharmacotherapy. 2007 Apr;27(4):510-8. doi: 10.1592/phco.27.4.510. PMID: 17381377.\n\nTrojand T, Morgan J, Shamoun CJ. Using the Modified Minnesota Detoxification Scale to Evaluate Alcohol Withdrawal Syndrome: An Integrative Review. Crit Care Nurse. 2025 Apr 1;45(2):60-68. doi: 10.4037/ccn2025568. PMID: 40168010.",
      "en": "The Modified Minnesota Detoxification Scale (mMINDS) is used to assess the severity of alcohol withdrawal symptoms. The score helps guide pharmacologic interventions for managing withdrawal. "
    }
  },
